

    ● It is a Continuous Integration /
    Continuous Deployment tool written in Java.
    ● It is used to build and test your
    software projects continuously making it easier for
    developers to integrate changes to the project,
    and making it easier for users to obtain a up-to date product.

    ● You can automate the build and testing, and also schedule it.

    ● Jenkins has 3 components:
    ○ Code Change: Devs makes changes to the application code
    ○ Test: CI tool automatically picks up the changes and tests the application
    ○ Deploy: CI tool deploys the application with changes